1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 4425 By: Hilbert
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to torts; creating the Oklahoma Tort
Reform Act of 2026; providing for noncodification;
8 and providing an effective date.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
13 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
14 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Oklahoma Tort
15 Reform Act of 2026".
16 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
